Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.34,0:01:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at these three guys here.\NHere's some more.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.37,0:01:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my god, another big one.\NAnd another big one.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.37,0:01:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NIt's like Giants.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.37,0:01:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like Giants.\NHi, hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.85,0:01:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got big guys today, Doc.\NBoy, oh boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.93,0:01:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like basketball day, eh?\NGood morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.09,0:01:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYou're from where?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.42,0:02:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan.\NOh, Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.31,0:02:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHi, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.09,0:02:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NTeamwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.09,0:02:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOh, look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.09,0:02:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that.\NLook at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.97,0:02:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that.\NLook at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.97,0:02:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that.\NLook at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.97,0:03:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.97,0:03:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace be with you.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.97,0:03:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Doc.\NHi, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.03,0:03:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?\NGood morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.03,0:03:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.49,0:03:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Doc.\NGood morning, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.49,0:03:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Have we gotten everybody?\NDid we get everybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.49,0:03:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Gloria and Excelsior Steel.\NThat's not comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.46,0:03:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the exit.\NAll the books that I've written, I put that on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.06,0:04:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,put that on one of the front pages, you know, to warn people. They ignore the warning, and\Nthen they write me these indignant emails. I warned you right in the beginning. Keep
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.75,0:04:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,out the riffraff. I try to cut out the riffraff at the opening pages. How many people are\Nnew here for the first time? Uh-huh. Okay. All right. So we try to balance the program
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.24,0:04:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on, you know, the balance of new people with regular attendees. For those that\Nare new, we recapitulate many of the charts and things, but we go through them a little
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.85,0:04:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,faster than usual. And then we always leave time for new charts and new understandings.\NSo we try to take care of it in that manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.33,0:04:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The best way to do that is to write a note.\NThe best way to learn is by repetition. Dr. Kallenbach always reminds me of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.82,0:05:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Repetition is the best teacher. And after you've heard a thing enough times, it becomes\Na part of you. You know, you just become, without thinking about it, it just becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.50,0:05:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,an assumption. So the repetition is not without its merit and benefit. What seems simple to\Npeople who have attended these lectures is quite confrontive to people who haven't. So
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.89,0:05:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore, we recapitulate some common ground, familiar ground, before we tackle the new.\NOne thing we always do is start with, well, we'll start with the slides. I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.95,0:06:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,how did Jesus make it without slides? I don't know. He had it written on the back of his hand,\NI don't know. And, blessed are the, well, I can talk spontaneously for an entire day
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.66,0:06:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,around the clock, so everybody knows that, so I don't need the charts. And the charts\Nare for self-discipline, so that I don't do that. Yeah. All right. So what I want to start
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.83,0:06:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with, then, is slide number one.\NYou can't give this lecture without slide number one. Right now, I'm reading books.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.87,0:06:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to have audio books. And so I'm going back to basics myself. I'm rereading\NPower vs. Force right now. That's the first one. I'm going to read all the books in a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.82,0:07:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,row. And it's fun going back over familiar territory. Except that you see the errors\Nyou made, you know, because 10 years later, you've accumulated a lot more information.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.52,0:07:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And the main error we made in Power vs. Force was that we didn't have the power to read\NPower vs. Force was the presumption that anybody could do the kinesiologic test for
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.85,0:07:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,truth. And the reason I arrived at that erroneous conclusion or impression was because we tried\Nit on, you know, a great number of people. And we did videotapes of it, et cetera. But
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.01,0:07:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,all the people that we tried it on were integrists. They all calibrated over 200. You know, friends\Nand associates and teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.98,0:07:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And spiritual students. We're all over 200. So naturally, it worked for everyone because\Nwe had a select group. But we weren't aware we had a select group. I was just presuming
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.13,0:08:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that they represented all of mankind, which is not so. We've discovered belatedly. So\Nthis is difficult. These people have had with the method is because that but in later, later
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.92,0:08:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,books, we're trying to correct that and point out that, frankly, the number of people who\Ncan do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.66,0:08:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,With any reliability is really quite limited, actually, you know, to a small percentage\Nof the world population. However, a group like this attracts people who are over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.20,0:08:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So for a group like this, the majority of people will be able to do it. And then there's\Na peculiarity that some people can't do it, like some people can't ride a bicycle, so
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.38,0:08:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,people can't sing, you know what I mean? Not everybody is born with every gift, you see.\NI was aware of that. I was watching the Winter Olympics.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.08,0:08:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everybody is born with certain talents, you see.\NThey do things I wouldn't even think of doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.62,0:08:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Downhill speed with your skull as the wind...\NI look at their exposed skull, not even a helmet on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.91,0:09:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say, God, it's going to be one mess if they hit the wall.\NCourage or foolishness, it's hard to know which.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.26,0:09:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But I love the Olympics because of the integrity\Nand because of the inner strength and valor of the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.86,0:09:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Inner strength and valor, yeah?\NTo put yourself out there like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.05,0:09:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we arrived with the map of consciousness,\Nand this evolved rather spontaneously, and I've told the story before,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.10,0:09:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was using, I learned kinesiology from John Diamond,\Nand I was testing it out on...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.70,0:09:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,staff at the clinic back east,\Nand we made certain discoveries.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.20,0:09:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When I went to teach it to people, I was looking for students.\NI was going to give a class on kinesiology that night,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.49,0:10:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and certain things make everybody go weak,\Nlooking at fluorescent lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.96,0:10:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can take anybody, have them look at fluorescent lights,\Nthey're weak, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.99,0:10:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Whole sweet and low over their solar plexus or pesticide,\Nand I grabbed these...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.72,0:10:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,folks, because they were just around the clinic.\NWe had an attitudinal healing center,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.12,0:10:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and when I went to test them, they didn't go weak.\NI said, whoa, what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.98,0:10:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody goes weak with fluorescent lights,\Nbut these spiritual students did not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.53,0:10:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we discovered that as your consciousness rises,\Nyour kinesiologic response is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.79,0:10:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So we tested that group, we tested a new group of students\Nin the Course in Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.12,0:10:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and they all went weak with fluorescent lights,\Net cetera, in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.62,0:10:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And then after a few months, none of them went weak.\NSo we saw, I said, wow, wow, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.30,0:11:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There's been a major shift in consciousness\Nin the acupuncture system.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.34,0:11:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole person's energy system had shifted.\NSo that's how we came upon this discovery,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.47,0:11:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and then later calibrated it and put it on a logarithmic scale\Nof one to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.63,0:11:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just want to recapitulate that,\Nthat not everyone can do it, for reasons as yet unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.63,0:11:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There's probably karmic elements of which we are unaware also.\NPerhaps people who have violated the truth in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.39,0:11:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,are not allowed karmically to use it\Nuntil they've re-earned the right to use it, perhaps,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.91,0:11:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,something like that.\NAll right, anyway, on the map of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.86,0:11:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we created a logarithmic scale from one to a thousand.\NAnd then we discovered that at level 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.34,0:11:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the critical level,\Nlevel 200 made the difference between truth versus falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.34,0:12:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity versus non-integrity.\NAnd people are often worrying about what their level of consciousness is,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.75,0:12:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and they want us to calibrate them and all such.\NAnd I tell them, the only thing you've got to worry about is to get over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.75,0:12:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Get over 200, and then forget about it,\Nbecause how can you measure devotion, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.75,0:12:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,18 pounds of devotion, 16 pounds of devotion,\Nhow can you measure commitment?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.77,0:12:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All the things that count, you know, are not really measurable.\NA prevailing level of consciousness, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.13,0:12:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,influences how you see and experience the world.\NAnd as perception, down here, perception rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.53,0:12:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we go up, perception becomes less and less dominant.\NAnd instead, we have vision,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.53,0:12:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because we begin to discern the essence,\Nwhich is the difference between the linear and the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.53,0:13:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with skeptics is because they are stuck in the linear\Nand certain fundamental materialism.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.04,0:13:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you move up the scale,\Nthe field becomes more and more undifferentiated.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.03,0:13:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes diffuse.\NIt becomes an overall ambiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.03,0:13:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes, eventually, a way of being.\NSo, these lower levels, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.10,0:13:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,these lower levels,\Ndominate half the people in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.46,0:13:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Half the people, 49%.\NAnd 85% of people in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.15,0:13:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, knowing that\Ntempers how you respond to the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.74,0:14:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You need that information\Nin order to handle watching the nightly news.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.74,0:14:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, the view of God, the view of oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.17,0:14:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,These levels all have names.\NMost of the people in this group are familiar with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.17,0:14:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,These logs are just a shorthand way of saying it.\NThis is the emotion that goes with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.34,0:14:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the process going on in consciousness itself.\NAll the way from
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.40,0:14:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the very bottom,\Nenslavement to being freed,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.60,0:14:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,revelation,\Nall the way to illumination
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.60,0:14:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and, eventually, enlightenment.\NSo, we're all familiar with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.70,0:14:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody have any questions about it?\NSpeak, or forever hold your peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.87,0:14:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not send me any e-mails about this.\NNext.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.94,0:14:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said, easy.\NThere wasn't any e-mails.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.94,0:15:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There wasn't any computers.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.91,0:15:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't come back again.\NSo, I said, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.65,0:15:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, with the Internet,\Nthat's not number two.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.12,0:15:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That scale, what?\NIs that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.46,0:15:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody's been fooling around my slides.\NThat scale goes up to 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.58,0:15:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This scale starts at 600.\NAt 600, there's the transformation of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.58,0:15:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and the levels of enlightenment.\NBegin at 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.58,0:15:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And these we've written about\Nin a book coming out at the end of the year,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.58,0:16:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotional Non-duality.\NAnyway, enlightenment, these are the expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.58,0:16:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of these we recognize\Nas the teachers of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.67,0:16:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are the great avatars\Nout of which
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.74,0:16:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the world's religions have emerged.\NAnd then, beyond that,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.74,0:16:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,are the even higher states,\Nsuch as archangels, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.97,0:16:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one thought.\NIf an archangel notices you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.97,0:16:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like you just hit a brick wall\Nat 100 miles an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.05,0:16:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and your life is totally changed.\NEnormous power.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.05,0:16:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,50,000 and up we calibrated them.\NOh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.10,0:16:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the next slide.\NThis was done for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.91,0:16:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This shows the rise of power\Nof the...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.91,0:16:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,as you go up the scale.\NNext one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.01,0:16:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.\NNext one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.04,0:17:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Because these are familiar,\Nwe won't spend a lot of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.04,0:17:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This is 78% of the world's population,\Nyou see, is below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.04,0:17:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the great mass of people.\NAnd therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.04,0:17:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to be even spiritually interested\Nor committed, you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.04,0:17:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you belong to the minority.\NBelong to the minority.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.36,0:17:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is how it looks on a graphic.\NYou see, in the 22% of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.36,0:17:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that are calibrated over 200,\Ncounterbalance is 78%
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.36,0:17:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that is below 200.\NOtherwise, the world would self-destruct,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.40,0:17:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or civilization would self-destruct.\NSo the challenges to our current civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.40,0:17:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,are coming from this group of people here.\NOkay, next.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.55,0:17:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NThis is Daniel Lyons.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.49,0:17:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel Lyons made this for us\Nand sent it to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.49,0:18:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the evolution of consciousness\Non a time scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.48,0:18:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,People say,\Nwhat do you think is the future of mankind?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.48,0:18:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is the level of consciousness\Nover great expanses of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.48,0:18:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Percent of elapsed time.\NYou can see 90% or 85% of elapsed time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.56,0:18:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it was still way down here,\Nand suddenly it took off.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.56,0:18:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see, despite the world news,\Nthat it's on a very upbeat,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.56,0:18:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,rampant rise.\NPeople lament, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.33,0:18:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,what they consider to be catastrophes in the world,\Nnot realizing that catastrophes themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.33,0:18:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,can be of great service to spiritual evolution.\NNothing gets you closer to God
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.51,0:18:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,than facing the muzzle of a gun.\NDuring World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.59,0:18:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the two of us sang,\Nand they're looking at a live mine
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.59,0:19:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,about to go off.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.46,0:19:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either God or nothing, I'll tell you.\NSo, in that instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.66,0:19:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you surrender your life, and so.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.91,0:19:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, calamity.\NSee, everybody laments and wrings their hands
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.91,0:19:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,about calamity.\NBut calamity is the only way
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.91,0:19:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,many people can get there.\NMany people cannot get there
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.49,0:19:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so long as life is smooth, prosperous, etc.\NAnd materialism disappears,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.54,0:19:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly,\Nwhen you're facing death, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.54,0:19:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThis is the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.33,0:19:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so spectacular\Nthat we repeat it every lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.33,0:19:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, throughout time,\Nhow consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.63,0:19:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,if we go all the way back\Nmulti-millions or billions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.63,0:19:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and track it over the millennia,\Nyou see how the scale of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.63,0:20:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,moves on.\NFirst signs of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.43,0:20:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,bacteria and algae,\Nat that point,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.50,0:20:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,approximately 70% of Earth time\Nhad already,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.50,0:20:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,70% of the planetary time\Nhad already evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.50,0:20:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,before the first bacteria appeared\Nat calibration level one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.50,0:20:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The interface of consciousness\Nin organic matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.00,0:20:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we'll move next.\NHow the atheist can explain
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.38,0:20:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,how organic arises from non-organic,\Nhow does organic arise from non-organic,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.56,0:20:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and how does life arise from non-life?\NWithout divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.59,0:20:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you're pretty stuck for an answer.\NWell, it just sort of happened, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.59,0:20:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And the animal kingdom followed\Nthat evolution of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.01,0:20:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and there you see the most ancient animals,\Nlife forms,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.01,0:21:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated extremely low,\Nand then they evolve,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.01,0:21:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and we keep getting higher and higher.\NWe get to the point
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.01,0:21:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,where we say,\Nwe get to the level of vipers,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.77,0:21:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Komodo dragons,\Nreptiles,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.81,0:21:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera,\Nthe predatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.00,0:21:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, there's corollaries\Nin the human domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.00,0:21:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people walking around,\Nin fact, they get big headlines,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.00,0:21:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they calibrate the same\Nas a Komodo dragon,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.00,0:21:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and their effect on your life\Nwill be identical.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.32,0:21:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have rodents.\NRodents actually calibrate higher
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.71,0:21:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,than serial killers.\NSerial killers,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.45,0:21:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you see them on TV all the time,\Ncalibrate around 35.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.45,0:21:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better to be a rodent.\NIt's better to be a rhinoceros.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.45,0:21:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Even a grizzly bear.\NYeah, but I wouldn't fool around with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.45,0:21:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or water buffaloes either.\NAnd then we get up to hippopotamus,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.57,0:22:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,who, as we've said before,\Nstatistically kills more people
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.57,0:22:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,than any other wild animal.\NYou wouldn't think so,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.57,0:22:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but I guess people are careless\Nabout hanging out with hippopotamuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.30,0:22:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I see them on TV from Africa.\NThey're there in a canoe
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.30,0:22:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,going by the hippopotamus,\Nand I think, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.56,0:22:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you finally get\Nto consciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.56,0:22:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as in mankind.\NThere's a shift of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.56,0:22:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You go from the predator\Nto the herbivore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.56,0:22:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we have the zebra,\Nthe gazelle, the giraffe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.66,0:22:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You see at 200 and up,\Nyou don't have to kill other living beings
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.66,0:22:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to survive.\NSo the deer, the bison, the elk,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.66,0:22:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,these are all benign,\Nrelatively benign.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.92,0:22:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, if they get mad at you,\Nthey can give you a hard time,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.92,0:22:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but in and of themselves,\Nthey're relatively benign.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.92,0:22:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Cats at 240, dogs at 245.\NAnd once you adopt an animal,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.01,0:23:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,its consciousness jumps five or ten points.\NAnd then you get to gorillas,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.14,0:23:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,some of whom we love,\Nhave become very famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.14,0:23:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Some famous gorillas.\NI think the one of the mother gorilla
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.14,0:23:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,picking up the child\Nwho fell into her domain there in a zoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.14,0:23:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Gently picked up this child\Nand put the child aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.14,0:23:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very heartwarming.\NEverybody remember that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.14,0:23:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.\NVery heartwarming.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.14,0:23:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So here was at 275.\NNow the exceptions, we said,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.40,0:23:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,there are some animals\Nthat calibrate as intelligent,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.40,0:23:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,actually can think.\NThere are black crows,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.40,0:23:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,who can figure out\Nhow to analyze problems
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.40,0:23:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and come up with solutions.\NGreat parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.40,0:23:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, Coco,\Nwe're all familiar with.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.40,0:23:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And the songbird's song at 500.\NThe cat's purr at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.52,0:23:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog's wagging tail at 500.\NThe capacity to respond,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.52,0:24:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to recognize love.\NOkay, so the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.68,0:24:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we went on to,\Nthat's the emotional level,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.68,0:24:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level.\NWhen you get to 400,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.97,0:24:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you get the level of the intellect.\NAnd so the great philosophers of all time,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.22,0:24:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was interesting\Nto calibrate all the great books
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.22,0:24:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Western world,\Nwhich I happily came into possession
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.48,0:24:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of a whole set.\NAnd you could spend a great deal of time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.78,0:24:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,reflecting on the implication\Nof these various people
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.78,0:24:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and their impact on the world and society.\NAnd they're almost all
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.92,0:24:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 400s\Nand some even in the high 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.07,0:24:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And those,\Nin amongst these books,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.07,0:24:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,there was one person\Nand then maybe even two
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.10,0:24:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that probably shouldn't have been there.\NEngels is certainly out of his realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.33,0:25:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all mid-400s.\NHe's at 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.33,0:25:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And Marx,\Nthe author of Relativism,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.33,0:25:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 130.\NNow without the,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.33,0:25:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,if you remove Marx and Engels,\Nthen the overall calibration jumps to 465,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.33,0:25:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,shows a major jump.\NSo even having one
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.33,0:25:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of a very low energy\Nand one that is marginal
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.33,0:25:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,brings down the overall level.\NAnd the impact of society
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.88,0:25:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,on relativistic thinking\Nhas been disastrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.98,0:25:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We just came out of the Cold War\Nand Vietnam
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.14,0:25:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and Communist China\Nand all the devastation we've seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.49,0:25:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Multi,\Nmulti millions of people dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.49,0:25:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So people can say,\Noh, this is very intellectual.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.80,0:25:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How can it be intellectual\Nwhen 100 million people die
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.80,0:25:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the impact of just this falsity?\NHardly,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.80,0:26:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the intellect and politics and philosophy\Nare not irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.96,0:26:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They determine\Nthe nature of our society.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.96,0:26:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay,\Nso,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.08,0:26:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we'll go to the next.\NYes,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.20,0:26:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,well,\Nthis is the relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.20,0:26:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,between context\Nand content.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.20,0:26:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nthis is very important to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.68,0:26:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is linear,\Nthis is definable,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.68,0:26:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and the lower mind comprehends this.\NThen,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.77,0:26:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,this event, however,\Noccurs in
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.77,0:26:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,approximate field.\NThat's recognized
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.13,0:26:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with situational\Nethics.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.13,0:26:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also recognized in court\Nthat what happens here
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.31,0:26:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is also influenced\Nby the approximate field,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.31,0:26:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,events surrounding it.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.31,0:26:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,what would be,\Nlet's say,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.31,0:27:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a,\Nwhat would be a limitation of liberty
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.63,0:27:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on\Nthe context.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.63,0:27:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In peacetime,\Nit would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.63,0:27:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In wartime,\Nit would just be survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.63,0:27:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So whether we say\Na thing is ethical
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.63,0:27:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,or unethical,\Ngood or bad,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.63,0:27:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,legal or illegal,\Na crime or not a crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.63,0:27:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on the situation,\Nand even courts,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.63,0:27:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of course,\Nacknowledge the influence
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.63,0:27:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of the situation.\NThese,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.07,0:27:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in turn,\Nthen,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.29,0:27:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,are within the overall\Ninfinite context
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.29,0:27:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness itself.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.29,0:27:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the most powerful,\Nthe most dominant,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.29,0:27:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,this becomes influential,\Nand this is the sequencing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.29,0:27:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we see within the linear domain.\NWe see this sequencing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.72,0:27:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,within the linear domain,\Nbut we're not always aware
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.72,0:27:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of this,\Nand most people forget
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.72,0:27:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,about this altogether.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.72,0:27:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.96,0:27:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we just did a diagram of it,\Nand we could go back,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.96,0:28:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,go over it again,\Nand this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.96,0:28:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,use,\Nsay,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.96,0:28:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the,\Nin the center of the diagram
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.96,0:28:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is the ego,\Nit's linear,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.96,0:28:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it's limited,\Nit's predictable,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.96,0:28:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,definable,\Nand that's the Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.96,0:28:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigm of reality,\Nwhich is measurable,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.96,0:28:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,yes,\Nand provable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.22,0:28:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The proximate field,\Nthe somewhat bigger field,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.07,0:28:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,can be understood\Nas semi-linear,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.07,0:28:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,semi-limited.\NIt's random,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.07,0:28:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,non-linear,\Nidentifiable,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.07,0:28:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,describable,\Nbut it's more diffuse
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.07,0:28:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and generalized.\NThe overall infinite context,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.07,0:28:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the,\Nwhat we drive to,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.07,0:28:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in,\Nin all these classes,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.07,0:28:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,what we're trying to do\Nis reach
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.29,0:28:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,this infinite context\Nto realize
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.29,0:28:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.29,0:28:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not,\Nit's not,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.29,0:28:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not,\Nit's not,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.29,0:28:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not,\Nit's not,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.29,0:28:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not,\Nit's not,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.29,0:28:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not,\Nit's not,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.29,0:28:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not,\Nand it's not,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.46,0:28:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not,\Nit's not,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.46,0:28:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not,\Nbut it's not,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.46,0:28:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,nor been created\Nfrom the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.46,0:28:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's 들어�able\Nof the furious life
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.77,0:29:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of life,\Nof being,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.77,0:29:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,not of living,\Nof Dob life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.84,0:29:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now remember,\Nwe have two more
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.84,0:29:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,states\Nthat can try
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.84,0:29:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,toapple\Nthe full
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.84,0:29:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,value\Nof reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.88,0:29:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one\Nfollows
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.77,0:29:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Text 1\Nbecomes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.46,0:29:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,non-local, knowable.\NOkay, that takes us through a great deal of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.94,0:29:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual foundations.\NPeople say, we get all kinds of emails, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.92,0:29:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,what can I do to advance myself?\NAnd I say, well, you can begin by behaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.85,0:29:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be polite, yeah?\NBut these are things that you don't have to become a,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.47,0:29:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to join an ashram.\NYou don't have to shave your head and wear sandals.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.82,0:30:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to take any oaths or commit yourself.\NThese are things that uplift you more than you realize.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.48,0:30:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,To be available to others, to be considerate.\NJust being considerate, you see, to,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.21,0:30:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it's very, it's loving to acknowledge other people.\NJust to acknowledge them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.92,0:30:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can experiment with that in clerks in various stores.\NAnd you see, the minute you smile appreciatively and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.57,0:30:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,gee, thank you, they just go, bong.\NI mean, in other words, it's,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.79,0:30:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to do so is less common than you would think.\NYou would think everybody would thank people for their service.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.74,0:30:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've noticed that people are quite bowled over by it.\NSo it must not be that common.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.94,0:30:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And to just try to be decent and reliable,\Nhonest, put in hard work, moral and ethical,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.86,0:31:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to be, you know, relatively kind, easygoing, thoughtful,\Nto be relatively open, as the suggestion of others, tolerant.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.63,0:31:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You lose your calm, but you come back to it because calmness is where you're happy.\NYou're happy with calm, and you're not happy with upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.24,0:31:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to be respectful of life and cordial towards it, friendly to others.\NSo these are all the common things that people say, well, I know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.29,0:31:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They know about that.\NBut if you look over them again, it is never too late to re-look at them
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.30,0:31:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and see where could I be more, perhaps this.\NOr maybe this, I'm not expressing my appreciation to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.13,0:31:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Expressing your appreciation to others is very important.\NSo we look to see where perhaps we're not being as diplomatic as we could.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.50,0:32:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't want to be wishy-washy, as nice as one thing and firm as something else.\NNicely firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.50,0:32:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you will have to pay your income tax this year.\NThey're friendly about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.14,0:32:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Many years ago, I was audited twice by the IRS, many years ago, back in the 70s or something.\NAnd it was a taxpayer compliance audit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.42,0:32:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was a taxpayer compliance audit. And it was a taxpayer compliance audit.\NAnd it was a taxpayer compliance audit. And it was a taxpayer compliance audit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.11,0:32:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was a taxpayer compliance audit.\NAnd it was a taxpayer compliance audit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.40,0:32:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was a taxpayer compliance audit.\NAnd I got it once, I got it two years in a row.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.49,0:32:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And, but it turned out to be a wonderful time.\NI laid things out elaborately for the tax man when he came.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.80,0:32:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And coffee and tea, and I had everything laid out so he could explain it.\NAnd he was just wowed. He went away really happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.10,0:32:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And the best time I was making an appointment with him was Friday afternoon,\Nbecause I got to get back to the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.59,0:32:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,By 4 o'clock I get started.\NBy 4 o'clock I get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.75,0:32:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,By 4 o'clock I get started.\Nhe was getting itchy feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.25,0:33:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's a little cleverness\NI throw in for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.22,0:33:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to audit you\Nand do it at home
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.72,0:33:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,until 4 in the afternoon.\NThe next year,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.73,0:33:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,by God,\Nthe computer picked me out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.36,0:33:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The likelihood of getting\Npicked out twice
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.02,0:33:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,was one in a couple of million.\NAnd I got it twice in a row.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.00,0:33:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And the second time\Nwas just as sanguine.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.03,0:33:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They were just wonderful.\NThey were very nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.90,0:33:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They were very polite.\NIt was a very positive
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.83,0:33:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,interchange.\NI really enjoyed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.75,0:33:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought they were\Nquite respectful.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.88,0:33:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course,\Nwho you are, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.42,0:33:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is influencing\Nhow they behave.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.94,0:33:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you act antagonistic\Nand argumentative
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.70,0:33:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and oppositional,\Nthen you'll trigger that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.42,0:33:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in the person.\NSo what you try to do
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.55,0:33:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is help the other person\Naccomplish their job
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.03,0:33:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to the best\Nthat can be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.59,0:33:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So to be as helpful\Nto the clerk,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.38,0:33:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,be as helpful\Nto the auditor,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.07,0:33:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll say the headsman.\NWhen he's going to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.64,0:33:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,chop your head off,\Nyou tell him,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.77,0:34:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,look, don't be nervous.\NIt's your job.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.51,0:34:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I got complete and total\Nfaith in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.50,0:34:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's a few bucks\Nthat will,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.57,0:34:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to make him\Nthe best headsman
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.44,0:34:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for the crown.\NYou see?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.28,0:34:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next.\NYes, even in that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.46,0:34:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of a situation.\NIn fact, there it's
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.07,0:34:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,even more important.\NDon't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.55,0:34:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there,\Nyou're being pressured
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.05,0:34:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to violate, you know,\Nyour own integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.44,0:34:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, don't violate.\NThe more you violate,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.80,0:34:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the more extreme\Nthe condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.57,0:34:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the less you give in\Nto it,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.59,0:34:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to violating it.\NThese are the,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.46,0:34:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,what the mind does,\N99% of the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.23,0:34:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is silent.\NSo the important thing we,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.88,0:34:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple of important\Nthings we teach.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.17,0:34:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing is that\Nthere is no such thing
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.21,0:34:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,as cause and effect.\NThat's a mentation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.98,0:34:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that you project\Nonto phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.86,0:34:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,within the world.\NIt does not exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.82,0:34:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no cause\Nin the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.78,0:35:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, what happens\Nis potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.21,0:35:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,emerges\Nand emerges.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.73,0:35:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're seeing\Nhappening is more like
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.46,0:35:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the butterfly emerging\Nfrom the cocoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.76,0:35:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the cocoon\Ndoesn't cause
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.26,0:35:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the butterfly.\NThe naive person says,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.23,0:35:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, look,\Nthe cocoon caused
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.57,0:35:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the butterfly.\NBecause it's antecedent
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.61,0:35:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean that\Nit's causative,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.51,0:35:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nand that's a basic fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.71,0:35:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Because one thing\Nprecedes another
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.57,0:35:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,does not mean\Nthat it's causal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.90,0:35:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It means it's in a\Npotentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.57,0:35:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's in a\Nreality emerging
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.09,0:35:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,as a witnessable\Nactuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.36,0:35:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Underneath the mind,\Nthen,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.48,0:35:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,underneath the mind\Nis silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.34,0:35:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind comes out\Nof silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.63,0:35:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Underneath the thinkingness.\NYou'll notice
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.48,0:35:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the thinkingness\Nis really superficial.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.71,0:36:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll notice that\Nif you begin to look
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.38,0:36:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,at the silence\Nunderneath the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.75,0:36:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The silence does not\Nprecede the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.01,0:36:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It underlies it.\NJust like the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.59,0:36:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,ocean underlies\Nthe flying fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.61,0:36:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can,\Neven as I'm talking now,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.67,0:36:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,don't worry about\Nthe talking
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.30,0:36:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the words\Nand understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.11,0:36:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget that.\NJust pay attention
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.32,0:36:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to the fact that\Nunderneath the listening
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.15,0:36:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and the talking\Nand the conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.67,0:36:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the mentation,\Nthat your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.30,0:36:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually silent.\NIn fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.13,0:36:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,99% of your mind\Nis silent all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.19,0:36:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 1%\Nis paying attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.00,0:36:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't pay\Nattention to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.30,0:36:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not feel\Noffended at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.26,0:36:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignore the speaker.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.46,0:36:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're automatically\Npicking it up
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.42,0:36:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time anyway.\NYou're always being
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.03,0:36:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,programmed.\NUnconsciously,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.00,0:36:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you're constantly\Nbeing programmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.71,0:36:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nwhat you do
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.57,0:36:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is you focus\Non the non-linear
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.78,0:36:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,field\Nin which the phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.57,0:37:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,are seen to be occurring\Nor are being witnessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.05,0:37:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That infinite field\Nof silence
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.61,0:37:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is present\Nright now.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.53,0:37:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I want everybody\Nto stop thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.94,0:37:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,this instant\Nand I want you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.67,0:37:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to notice\Nthat underneath
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.67,0:37:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,all the thinkingness\Nwhen it stops
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.05,0:37:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is silence.\NThere's silence
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.28,0:37:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,underneath the mind.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.26,0:37:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the silence\Nin this room
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.38,0:37:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,remains\Neven though
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.23,0:37:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,there's\Nvoice and sound
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.71,0:37:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,vibrations.\NBut the silence
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.48,0:37:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,itself,\Nthe silence itself
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.38,0:37:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is unaffected.\NIt's like
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.05,0:37:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,if a tree\Ndrops in the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.96,0:37:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the silence\Nis still
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.23,0:37:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,unimpeded.\NBecause
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.65,0:37:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,if it wasn't\Nfor the silence,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.44,0:37:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you couldn't hear\Nthe tree fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.78,0:37:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because\Nof the silence,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.30,0:37:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the fact\Nthat your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.67,0:37:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is doing nothing\Nat all,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.63,0:37:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can\Neven think.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.25,0:37:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If the mind\Nwasn't silent,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.86,0:38:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,there'd be static\Nand you'd keep
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.13,0:38:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,saying,\Nwhat,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.76,0:38:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what,\Nwhat,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.46,0:38:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,what,\Nwhat,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.21,0:38:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,what,\Nwhat.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.48,0:38:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.13,0:38:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that\Nthe mind
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.53,0:38:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is 99%\Nsilent
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.05,0:38:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is not.\NIt's noticeable
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.23,0:38:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because the 1%\Nthat's active,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.15,0:38:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you are in a\Nhypnotic state.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.80,0:38:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,To get free\Nfrom the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.30,0:38:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to realize\Nthat you are
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.36,0:38:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in a hypnotic,\Nyou are hypnotized
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.90,0:38:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,by the 1%\Nof the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.21,0:38:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You think that\Nthis little TV
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.55,0:38:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,set going on\Ninside,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.90,0:38:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,here's a castle\Nwith 46 rooms
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.80,0:38:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and one little TV\Nover here
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.11,0:38:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're sitting\Nthere watching
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.17,0:38:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,this TV.\NIt's saying
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.36,0:38:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no,\Nno peace
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.63,0:38:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in this castle.\NSo this 1%,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.46,0:38:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it's because\Nyou're glamorized
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.03,0:38:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,by it.\NYou're glamorized
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.67,0:38:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,by it.\NYou're glamorized
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.23,0:39:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,by it.\NYou're seduced
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.82,0:39:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,by it.\NYou're seduced
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.71,0:39:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,by the interest\Nin the action.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.55,0:39:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing\Ngoing on
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.69,0:39:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in this whole\Ncastle of 54 rooms
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.94,0:39:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and 150 acres.\NThe only thing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.17,0:39:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that's happening\Naround here
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.59,0:39:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is in this\N4 by 6 inch
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.86,0:39:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,TV set.\NThis is all
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.84,0:39:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that's happening.\NThere's nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.90,0:39:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,happening.\NThere's nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.21,0:39:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,else happening.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.36,0:39:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A person gets\Nbored and the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.86,0:39:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,job says,\Nwhere's the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.13,0:39:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,TV set?\NSo that shows
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.90,0:39:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you how you're\Nhooked and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.15,0:39:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,addicted,\Naddicted to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.03,0:39:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy\Nof happening,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.98,0:39:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what's happening.\NSo this mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.13,0:39:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,1% has\Ngot you
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.88,0:39:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,hypnotized\Nand this is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.09,0:39:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what it's\Ndoing all the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.00,0:39:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,time.\NIt's romanticizing,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.96,0:39:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,moralizing,\Ncriticizing,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.63,0:39:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,dramatizing.\NIt loves
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.21,0:39:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,drama.\NVictims,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.61,0:39:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,catastrophe,\Nrationalize.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.32,0:39:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All this is what\Nit's glamorizing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.19,0:40:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,things.\NAnd in the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.94,0:40:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,meantime,\Nit's theorizing
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.11,0:40:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,about it,\Net cetera,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.26,0:40:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and criticizing\Nit,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.75,0:40:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,romanticizing it.\NSo you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.42,0:40:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,this is all\Nstuff that we're
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.69,0:40:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,putting on it.\NIt doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.01,0:40:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,exist there.\N1% doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.23,0:40:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,have any\Ngreat power
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.11,0:40:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of you.\NThe only
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.63,0:40:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,power it has\Nis the power
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.88,0:40:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you give it.\NSo you have
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.19,0:40:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to turn down\Nthe seduction,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.07,0:40:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the seduction\Nof the 1%
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.03,0:40:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of the\Nmind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.61,0:40:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's\Nseductive.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.88,0:40:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And realize\Nthat you're
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.11,0:40:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,hypnotized by\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.94,0:40:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you\Nhave that
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.67,0:40:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,knowledge,\Nit gives
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.57,0:40:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you a big\Nedge.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.84,0:40:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And getting\Nunhooked
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.55,0:40:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,from it.\NOkay,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.55,0:40:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the next\None.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.42,0:40:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nthis is how
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.34,0:40:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the world\Nthinks the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.25,0:40:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,thing happens.\NActually,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.34,0:40:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an\Nattractor
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.09,0:40:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,pattern held\Nin consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.42,0:40:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and we\Nproject that
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.44,0:40:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,onto the\Nphenomena.
