Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.47,1:20:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the teachings.\NAnd one thing that dawned on me this morning was,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.60,1:20:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,religions and spiritual teachers\Nput demands and obligations and pledges
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.19,1:20:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and God knows what on the students.\NBut you never hear the teacher make a statement
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.26,1:21:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and a pledge of what is his responsibility to the student.\NForget about the student's obligation to the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.03,1:21:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But the teacher's obligation,\Nthe teacher should make a statement of commitment.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.03,1:21:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Commitment to what?\NCommitment to integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.84,1:21:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Commitment to not exploit the students.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.06,1:21:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see the ravages that have occurred\Nin some of the world's most major religions
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.52,1:21:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,for a lack of integrity\Nand a statement of commitment of the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.55,1:21:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The teacher should first make a statement\Nthat I'm committed to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.17,1:21:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm committed to the highest truth.\NAnd I also make the commitment not to exploit
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.96,1:21:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the,\Nstudent-teacher relationship,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.13,1:21:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the prevalence of fallen\Ngurus is increasing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.50,1:22:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, we weren't even allowed to use\Nthe word in the last couple of books.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.22,1:22:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We asked if we used the word,\Nit said no.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.77,1:22:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The meaning of the word is meant to\Nexploit it, to exploit
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.03,1:22:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the student for money,\Npower, sex, control, God knows
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.38,1:22:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what. I think a teacher\Nshould stand up and make a declaration
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.80,1:22:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of intention and commitment\Nto the student,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.86,1:22:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,not just vice versa.\NI've run across fallen gurus
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.06,1:22:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in my lifetime, and I can\Nsee what the pitfalls are, and I can see
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.07,1:22:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,how easy it is.\NTherefore, in our own lectures,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.81,1:22:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,especially the calibration levels of the 500s,\Nwe try to warn
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.19,1:22:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,people of the downside\Nas you get
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.03,1:22:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,into the 500s, and especially\Nthe high 500s,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.73,1:23:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which is where most of the famous\Ngurus of the last
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.96,1:23:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,decade have gotten to before\Nthey fell.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.09,1:23:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Each level\Nhas its
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.86,1:23:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,weakness.\NBecause a group like this is going to have a lot of
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.27,1:23:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,people going into the high 500s,\Nand we've warned about
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.97,1:23:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the cities as they arise,\Nthe S-I-D-D-H-I-S,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.72,1:23:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the so-called paranormal\Nphenomena, supernormal,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.15,1:23:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever you want to call them,\Nwhich are a consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.42,1:23:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of the rise of the kundalini energy.\NIt's not personal,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.93,1:23:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not yours.\NYou can't sell it, buy it, and use it to manipulate
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.51,1:23:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,people, because you\Nthen fall into magic.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.39,1:23:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You fall into magic and manipulating things.\NThese phenomena, as you
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.34,1:23:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,grow spiritually,\Nthe miraculous becomes
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.31,1:23:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,more and more common.\NMore and more common.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.09,1:24:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The miraculous phenomena begin to occur\Nin and of themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.35,1:24:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In and of themselves.\NAnd if you're honest,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.60,1:24:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll realize it is not the personal\Nyou at all that has anything to do
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.57,1:24:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,with it. These phenomena\Nare occurring of their own.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.97,1:24:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy goes out,\Naccomplishes the miraculous,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.65,1:24:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're the witness.\NThere's no miracle workers.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.46,1:24:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No person\Nwho then causes a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.02,1:24:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd all the phenomena that are
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.97,1:24:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,associated with the cities\Nare spontaneous.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.78,1:24:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They all arise.\NThey last for a number of years.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.93,1:24:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Some are quite incredible.\NNot even capable of description.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.46,1:24:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You can really hold the thing in mind.\NThe phenomena happens.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.22,1:24:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're on the city street.\NJust the thought of a taxi cab
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.80,1:25:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,arises in your mind,\Nand a limousine pulls up.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.73,1:25:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it twice with a\Nwell-known spiritual teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.85,1:25:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He said,\Nhow did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.31,1:25:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you do that?\NIt isn't an I that did that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.93,1:25:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when we left\Nthe lecture,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.77,1:25:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the phenomena was,\Nhe said, well, let's see if you can do it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.14,1:25:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, a big brown limousine pulled up.\NThat guy opened the door.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.10,1:25:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We always got a parking space\Nright next to the Lincoln Center.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.17,1:25:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Our first one.\NHold in mind you need a parking space.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.80,1:25:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And just as you get there, the car pulls out,\Nand there you've got the nearest parking space,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.15,1:25:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Lincoln Center.\NBut that was continuous.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.64,1:25:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a phenomena.\NThose phenomena occur in high-five nights.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.48,1:25:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.00,1:26:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to beware of glamorization.\NNot to fall for the seduction of the phenomena,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.43,1:26:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and think that you are the perpetrator of that phenomena.\NClairvoyance, clairaudience, all those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.21,1:26:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Distant viewing.\NYou can go inside a locked box,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.42,1:26:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,read what's there,\Ncome back out again,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.77,1:26:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and read it and tell people what's in the box.\NThose are phenomena that occur as a consequence of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.09,1:26:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is to be respectful, thankful for the field,\Nand never to claim it as your own.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.18,1:26:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you're going to be stuck on the other side\Nas one of those entities.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.00,1:26:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They've been there a couple thousand years.\NI feel they should move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.77,1:26:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody tells me who they're, what do you call that,\Non the other side?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.72,1:26:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Who they're channeling.\NYeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.78,1:26:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Channeling.\NChanneling.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.75,1:26:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, well, tell whoever it is on the other side,\Nit's time they move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.34,1:27:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Get off the ego trip of channeling.\NSome of them have been at it a thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.14,1:27:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You can ask, how long has this entity been at it?\NEver since Mesopotamia.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.47,1:27:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then I wanted to finish that with spiritual teachers.\NDon't trust the teacher who's not willing to commit to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.93,1:27:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all interested in your committing to them,\Nand controlling your life, and squeezing you for whatever they can get out of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.32,1:27:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And because it's become so common, so common,\NI felt it should be spoken about.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.56,1:27:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was thinking about it this morning.\NDo I know of a teacher who's committed themself to the student?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.68,1:27:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, I don't know of a teacher who commits themself to the student.\NIt's always the other way around.
