Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.96,1:38:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so consciousness is\Nby its own design
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.06,1:38:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,intrinsically innocent\Nbecause it does not inherently have
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.03,1:38:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to tell truth from falsehood\Nthe interest in truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.27,1:38:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,arises as consciousness\Nlevel rises
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.50,1:38:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and again it becomes a propensity\Nand a likelihood
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.50,1:38:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but not a cause and effect relationship\Nthe sense of the self
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.50,1:38:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with a capital S\Nis a subtlety
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.63,1:38:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,an awareness of the field\Nand this sense arises independently
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.81,1:38:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of the personal sense of I\Nthat which is called I
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.10,1:38:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs spontaneously within the field\Nbut it's spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.32,1:39:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs within the field\Nit's not a decision
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.00,1:39:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't decide whether or not\Nyou can experience your distances
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.00,1:39:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I\Nit's already a given
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.00,1:39:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,or you wouldn't be a human being\NI think human beings
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.31,1:39:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,get born here\Nbecause they're stuck with a sense of I
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.31,1:39:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that claims\Nclaims credit for everything
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.31,1:39:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,claims authorship\Nand therefore this world then
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.31,1:39:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is to undo that illusion\Nto undo the illusion
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.64,1:39:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are a separate independent\Nsource of causality
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.64,1:39:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a dualistic view of the world\Nso to transcend linearity and duality
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.77,1:39:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to me is the ultimate spiritual purpose\Nof human lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.77,1:39:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of human consciousness\Nis very slow
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.02,1:39:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet we see from the timetable\Nthat it's now exhilarating at a rapid rate
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.22,1:40:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,why?\Nbecause the combined spiritual intention
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.22,1:40:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is so powerful\Nit's not causal
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.22,1:40:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't cause things\Nto happen differently out there
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.22,1:40:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but our own spiritual intention\Nour own spiritual intention
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.92,1:40:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as I watch the people in the\Nin the winter olympics
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.46,1:40:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you see\Nand you see the incredible feet
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.52,1:40:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a triple axial\Nand then he falls
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.52,1:40:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I find myself automatically praying for him\NI just automatically pray for him
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.52,1:40:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,for his spirits\NI pray for his spirit
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.52,1:40:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because the courage that it takes\Nto put yourself out there
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.52,1:40:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in front of the TV land of the entire world\NI mean it takes courage
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.75,1:40:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes courage\Nso every time they fall
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.75,1:40:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I always pray for them\NI tell them that was beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.75,1:40:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that was wonderful\Nand I love you
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.75,1:40:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and God loves you\Npretty soon they'll be vying to fall on the ice
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.22,1:40:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and say I don't know\Nevery time I fall on the ice
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.22,1:41:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel so good\Nmillions of people all over the world
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.22,1:41:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,praying for him\Nyou know
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.22,1:41:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,wow I don't know\NI feel just swell
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.22,1:41:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,well I noticed they weren't crushed\Nthey weren't crushed
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.35,1:41:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,were they\Nand I think it is the spiritual intention
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.35,1:41:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of us witnessing them\Nand saluting their courage
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.35,1:41:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are not crushed\Nmost ordinary people
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.71,1:41:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,when they meet a major defeat\Nbecome crushed
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.71,1:41:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and dispirited\Ndo they not
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.71,1:41:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet to see these people\Npractically ignore it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.71,1:41:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and go right on with it\Nso I think myself
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.97,1:41:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it is the encouragement\Nand the energy we pour into these contestants
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.97,1:41:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,for the courage to get up there\Nand do what they do
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.53,1:41:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and then try things that are so difficult\Nand to try to be graceful and beautiful about it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.57,1:41:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time\NI think to do a triple axel
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.57,1:41:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and also be beautiful about it\Nis something else
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.57,1:42:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I could do a triple axel\Nbut I don't know how beautiful I'd be about it
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.57,1:42:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so I think our combined intention of integrity\Nencourages people
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.80,1:42:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so valor\Nvalor then attracts to it the energy
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.80,1:42:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that tends to increase valor\Nso spirituality also means valor
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.80,1:42:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it is often misinterpreted as passivity\Nand sort of the wet lily kind of spirituality
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.93,1:42:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I call it\Nno when the bearer walks up to you
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.43,1:42:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you better stand up to the bearer\Nit's time to pull your courage together
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.68,1:42:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and say oh lord I need help with this bearer\Nalright so then
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.36,1:42:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual evolution also means strength\Nstrength, courage, valor
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.36,1:43:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and it doesn't mean passivity\Npassivity you remember from
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.97,1:43:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,two verses faulty\NCalvary is quite low
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.97,1:43:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,passivity actually Calvary is very low\Nit's a misinterpretation
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.97,1:43:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because Christ said turn the other cheek\Nand that misinterpretation has come down through the centuries
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.19,1:43:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that spiritual integrity is passivity\Nso you have to reflect on what he meant
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.19,1:43:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,by that admonition\Nthe experience of the self then
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.69,1:43:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is first what you presume to be yourself\Nthat's always the starting point
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.69,1:43:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencer\Nno matter what we're experiencing
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.93,1:43:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we presume that's who we are\Nwhich always brings up the difficulty
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.02,1:43:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,between discerning perception from essence\Nwe're witnessing then is our perception
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.53,1:43:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and our perceptions\Nare preconceived images projected onto the world
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.53,1:44:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you differentiate essence from content\Nhow do you
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.60,1:44:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you tell which is content\Nwhich is a projection
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.60,1:44:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,which is illusion\Nand which is reality
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.81,1:44:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually with spiritual work\Nthat capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.81,1:44:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern\Nthe capacity for discernment
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.61,1:44:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,does develop and opens up\Nso that you can look at the thing
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.77,1:44:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you see what its image is\Nyou see how the world would see it
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.77,1:44:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and what the world would say about it\Nthink about it
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.77,1:44:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,value it\Nand you see its essence
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.77,1:44:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so when we see the performer\Nfall on the ice
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.77,1:44:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't witness him as a failure\Nwe don't witness him as a disgrace
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.77,1:44:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a passing regret\Nand he knew that he was taken out
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.77,1:44:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and at risk when he did that triple axial\Nwhen he did the second one
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.77,1:44:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because how strong are your ankles anyway\Nthey're only human ankles
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.80,1:44:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,alright\Nso we see the essence
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.80,1:45:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's what we applaud\Nis the essence
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.80,1:45:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage\Nthe valor
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.80,1:45:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,within the contestant\Nand of course they do the best they can
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.80,1:45:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's not what the whole game is\Nthe whole game is who they are
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.80,1:45:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so what we applaud is who they are\Nand their capacity to go out there
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.80,1:45:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and publicly state it\Nbecause they know the downside
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.80,1:45:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is like a hundred million people watching you\Nas you fall
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.80,1:45:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet they got the courage to face that\Nso what we discern now is essence
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.80,1:45:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,essence\Nit isn't
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.80,1:45:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really care what their scores are\NI never pay any attention to scores
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.80,1:45:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what I get is the heart of the person\Nyou get the heart of the people
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.80,1:45:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,as they are being what they are\Nto the fullest extent
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.80,1:45:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we salute traditionally\Nin the great games
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.96,1:46:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to get one up on the experiencer\Nthe perceiver
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.23,1:46:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is the trick\Nand the way it's done
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.46,1:46:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we started to talk about before the break\Nyou pull back
Dialogue: 0,1:46:09.56,1:46:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see you're not the content\Nyou're the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:46:12.56,1:46:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're the watcher\Nthen you are not even the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:46:16.01,1:46:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or the watcher\Nyou see that witnessing and watching
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.01,1:46:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is happening of its own\Nyou don't decide
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.01,1:46:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,oh I think I will witness and watch\Nthe phenomena of this world today
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.01,1:46:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not a decision you made at all\Nit's happening all of its own
Dialogue: 0,1:46:32.19,1:46:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see how the ego would jump in\Nand want to take credit
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.19,1:46:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so one way to define the\Nthe ego
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.19,1:46:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the small\Nthe self with a small s
Dialogue: 0,1:46:43.19,1:46:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is that which is constantly seeking\Nto own claim and take credit for
Dialogue: 0,1:46:49.89,1:46:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in actuality\Nit doesn't deserve any credit for anything
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.89,1:47:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not the author of anything\Nit's the witness at best the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.72,1:47:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the person will say well I am the observer\Nwhat I is observing
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.72,1:47:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there isn't any I observing\Nobserving is happening of observing this
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.72,1:47:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as a spontaneous autonomous phenomena\Nso phenomena are occurring
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.07,1:47:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,autonomously\Nas a consequence of emergence
Dialogue: 0,1:47:21.23,1:47:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said the cocoon\Nbecomes the butterfly
Dialogue: 0,1:47:25.23,1:47:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing causes it\Nin the experiential world then is
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.53,1:47:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,radical subjectivity\Nradical subjectivity
Dialogue: 0,1:47:36.77,1:47:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you look for the radical subjectivity\Nout of which you experience existence
Dialogue: 0,1:47:43.14,1:47:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencing of existence\Nthen you're only a step away
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.43,1:47:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to see that that which is\Nyou are
Dialogue: 0,1:47:52.07,1:47:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is the field out of which experiencing itself\Nis emerging
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.07,1:48:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can witness the eyes\Ngreediness
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.22,1:48:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,greediness\Nto claim
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.22,1:48:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is the author of all actions\Nand thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.22,1:48:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,etc\Nyou can watch its greediness
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.57,1:48:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,without joining the greediness\Nand you merely become witness
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.57,1:48:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of the personal I\Nyou become witness of the personal I
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.93,1:48:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody\Nyou can all do that
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.42,1:48:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,from this moment on you can all do that\Nthere
